{"source_key":"sha256-d1b343ed42a51085ffb3fbb074863c4f","record_index":3161,"record_hash":"sha256:45a7f148ca8302e97ca8f8ccd06e52f9ed6f006ea7c0a6cec0e715899915c0af","timestamp":"2026-06-04T22:32:56.867Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Most agentic `but` users are hybrid, not pure-agent.\n\nCohort: 664 mature users with first observed agentic `but commit` in last 180d, excluding last 14d. Retention = another agentic `but commit` in days 7-13.\n\n**Headline**\n- Desktop/manual UI mutation in week one: 507 users, 76.4%\n- No desktop/manual UI mutation: 157 users, 23.6%\n- Retention: 48.3% with desktop manual ops vs 22.3% without\n\nMore precise split:\n\n| Cohort | Users | Retention |\n|---|---:|---:|\n| Desktop manual only | 356, 53.6% | 46.9% |\n| Desktop + manual CLI writes | 151, 22.7% | 51.7% |\n| Manual CLI writes only | 44, 6.6% | 43.2% |\n| Agent-only | 113, 17.0% | 14.2% |\n\nSo pure agent-only is small and retains badly. Hybrid usage looks like the healthy path.\n\nTop desktop manual ops in week one:\n- Push: 65.5% of users\n- Integrate Upstream: 61.4%\n- Commit: 56.2%\n- Create Stack: 51.2%\n- Unapply Stack: 47.1%\n- Discard Changes: 46.5%\n- Rename branch: 40.7%\n- Amend Commit: 40.4%\n- Uncommit: 33.4%\n\nManual desktop commit specifically:\n- 373 users, 56.2%\n- retention 51.7%\n- users with desktop ops but no desktop commit: 20.2%, retention 38.8%\n- no desktop ops: 23.6%, retention 22.3%\n\nManual CLI is noisier because “no agent detected” includes junk like completions/hooks/refreshes. After filtering to write-ish commands, 29.4% do manual CLI writes. Main ones are `commit`, `rub`, `push`, `branchNew`, `branchUnapply`, `prNew`, `branchApply`.\n\nMy read: this is not “manual ops cause retention.” It’s more likely an activation signal. Users who understand GitButler enough to inspect, push, amend, uncommit, create stacks, or clean up manually are much more likely to keep using agentic commits. The product opportunity is probably to make the agent expose that workspace-control loop, not to push users into manual work.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-06-04T22:32:56.867Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}